01:45:14.460 --> 01:45:15.770
And this used to be the hand

01:45:15.770 --> 01:45:17.040
that was connected to their spouse.

01:45:17.040 --> 01:45:20.970
This may be a comment on
spouses more than on phones.

01:45:20.970 --> 01:45:25.970
But it sounds like it's a
kind of a security blanket

01:45:27.000 --> 01:45:27.833
of sorts.
- Right, like a

01:45:27.833 --> 01:45:29.160
transitional object, yeah.

01:45:29.160 --> 01:45:33.700
- Actually that reminds me,
you've referred to the phone,

01:45:33.700 --> 01:45:34.630
I think it's the phone,

01:45:34.630 --> 01:45:38.590
but maybe it's our online
persona or ourselves,

01:45:38.590 --> 01:45:41.923
as we've become sort of
infantile in our need for,

01:45:41.923 --> 01:45:43.699
it's like a baby and a bottle.

01:45:43.699 --> 01:45:44.532
- Right, right.

01:45:44.532 --> 01:45:46.780
- And so I do wonder if we have regressed,

01:45:46.780 --> 01:45:50.220
and I do think we've
regressed a bit in terms of

01:45:50.220 --> 01:45:51.900
our online behavior.

01:45:51.900 --> 01:45:54.010
Our inability to act like.

01:45:54.010 --> 01:45:55.070
I always thought an adult

01:45:55.070 --> 01:45:56.350
was somebody that can
control their behavior.

01:45:56.350 --> 01:45:57.340
- Yeah.
- That's the difference

